  <h2>What the deal does</h2>

  <p>Under the multiyear agreement, ArenaPlus will integrate official NBA branding across its online platforms, run localized marketing activations targeting Philippine basketball audiences, and receive integrated promotional features across the NBA's own digital and social channels in the country. The integration goes substantially beyond a passive sponsorship: the deal places ArenaPlus inside the NBA's Philippine consumer-engagement architecture rather than alongside it.</p>

  <p>The free-to-play product layer is structured around the NBA calendar. ArenaPlus launched the "Playoffs MVP: Battle for the Most Valuable Predictor" contest on March 21, 2026, in advance of the 2026 NBA Playoffs &mdash; a free-to-play bracket-style prediction game that allows participants to submit playoff picks and compete for prizes. The free-to-play wrapper is meaningful because it allows the partnership to engage Philippine NBA fans who are not active sportsbook customers, building the funnel for the regulated paid-product side of ArenaPlus.</p>

  <p>The free-to-play structure also navigates the post-August-2025 BSP e-wallet delinking environment cleanly. A free-to-play product does not need the in-app cashier flow that the delinking order removed; it can engage users on the NBA-brand basis alone and convert them into paid users through the slower, more deliberate ArenaPlus onboarding process. In a delinking-constrained environment, this is the right product architecture.</p>

  <h2>The market context</h2>

  <p>ArenaPlus has held the No. 1 position among PAGCOR-licensed online sportsbooks in the Philippines since its 2023 launch under DigiPlus Interactive. The platform's growth has been the single largest driver of the PIGO sports betting segment's overall expansion. PAGCOR's quarterly disclosures across 2025 documented sports betting growth at triple-digit rates year on year, with ArenaPlus capturing a disproportionate share of the new licensed market.</p>

  <p>The Q1 2026 financial picture is more complicated. DigiPlus's parent-level disclosure showed Q1 2026 net income down 33 percent year on year on revenue down 25 percent, with the August 2025 BSP e-wallet delinking order cited as the primary cause. ArenaPlus's contribution to the consolidated result is not separately disclosed in the parent filings, but the company's commentary has emphasized that the sports betting product proved more resilient to the delinking shock than the e-games products did. The NBA partnership extends that resilience by giving ArenaPlus a marketing and content tentpole that the delinked environment makes harder to assemble through pure direct-acquisition spending.</p>

